You need to manually inject/extract the W3C trace context into RabbitMQ message headers since the queue doesn't propagate it automatically.

**Service A (Publisher) — inject context:**

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;

var activitySource = new ActivitySource("ServiceA");
using var activity = activitySource.StartActivity("publish-order", ActivityKind.Producer);

var props = channel.CreateBasicProperties();
props.Headers = new Dictionary<string, object>();

// Inject current trace context into headers
if (Activity.Current != null)
{
    props.Headers["traceparent"] = Activity.Current.Id;
    props.Headers["tracestate"] = Activity.Current.TraceStateString ?? "";
}

channel.BasicPublish(exchange, routingKey, props, body);
```

**Service B (Consumer) — extract and link context:**

```csharp
var activitySource = new ActivitySource("ServiceB");

// In your consumer callback:
var headers = ea.BasicProperties.Headers;
ActivityContext parentContext = default;

if (headers?.TryGetValue("traceparent", out var raw) == true)
{
    var traceparent = Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])raw);
    ActivityContext.TryParse(traceparent, null, out parentContext);
}

using var activity = activitySource.StartActivity(
    "consume-order",
    ActivityKind.Consumer,
    parentContext);  // <-- links this span to the producer's trace
```

**Key points:**

1. Both services must register their `ActivitySource` with the OTel SDK (`AddSource("ServiceA")` / `AddSource("ServiceB")`).
2. RabbitMQ headers store `byte[]`, so encode/decode with `Encoding.UTF8`.
3. If you use MassTransit or NServiceBus, this is done automatically — the manual approach is only needed with the raw `RabbitMQ.Client`.
4. For the cleanest setup, use `DistributedContextPropagator.Current.Inject/Extract` instead of hand-rolling, which handles `tracestate` and baggage too:

```csharp
// Inject (publisher)
DistributedContextPropagator.Current.Inject(activity, props.Headers,
    (carrier, key, value) => ((IDictionary<string,object>)carrier)[key] = value);

// Extract (consumer)
DistributedContextPropagator.Current.ExtractTraceIdAndState(headers,
    (carrier, key) => {
        var h = (IDictionary<string,object>)carrier;
        return h.TryGetValue(key, out var v) ? Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])v) : null;
    },
    out var traceId, out var traceState);
```

This gives you a single end-to-end trace spanning both services through the queue.
